INSERT INTO `sandbox_comments` VALUES (18,2998,'Haiming','haiming@aplus.net.nz','http://www.aplus.net.nz','180.149.31.154','2014-04-28 09:08:07','2014-04-28 13:08:07','Mehraban, your post is really one of a category. I used 301 redirect to my old sites but was not aware that it would transfer some SEO benefits too. I use .htaccess to do it. I am sharing my .htaccess code with your fellow visitors in case they may need it. Here you go:\n\n<code>RewriteEngine on \nRewriteRule ^(.*)$ http://NewSiteName.com/$1 [R=301,L]</code>',0,'1','','',0,0);
INSERT INTO `sandbox_comments` VALUES (19,3004,'Claudio Heilborn','claudio@mdmarketingdigital.com','http://www.mdmarketingdigital.com','46.24.93.74','2014-05-09 07:00:08','2014-05-09 11:00:08','Hi Derek nice piece of work, I have always in mind a quote that we use thoroughly when starting to re-make a web:  “We can\'t solve problems by using the same kind of thinking we used when we created them” it´s definitely necessary to think before we act and we must take care to set our minds in a new environment when we are looking forward to “renew” something that has already been done once. \nYours is the correct mind setting for kicking off a new web. We must ask ourselves some questions, and set our goals. We always tell our clients that every effort and investment in Digital Marketing should have an object and ideally we should set KPI (key performance indicators) so as to be able to measure success or failure on achieving these goals and use these metrics to make all possible corrections. (eg navigation time, conversions, pages/visit, etc, keywords positioning in serps)\nI believe you have structured the thinking process which is basically shown in this article and I must point out something else from 3.   actually I believe that trends change so quickly… and we are obliged to look trendy always. Your target audience changes not only because a new target comes and navigates your site, it also changes because we change, we are different form the ones we were a couple of years before, and discover different resources after some time going by. Today in these rapidly changing times, if you want to look trendy you must include for example some parallax tricks in your website, this didn´t even exist some months ago, maybe one year ago…\nChanges are abrupt, in social media for example, changes are remarkable and modify our scope so quickly, and we must take care as these changes could affect our business and our customers business. \nFinally we find a huge risk, if we want to get, or stay, in the groove we can find the risk of a “never ending process” and never end our work, the appalling consequence would be never finishing our web! To look trendy is a race that never ends…\nSo maybe set a timetable, keep strict to this schema and stick to those times obliging yourself to finish on time. Now, for the future, set an ongoing process where we should start our thinking process as soon as we have finished our new web, so as to begin creating the next one… \nWriting this answer has bred on me the eagerness to write an article. Thanks for seeding, I´ll let you know if there is some good harvest! ;) \n\nCheers!',0,'1','','',0,0);
INSERT INTO `sandbox_comments` VALUES (20,3105,'Ashlie Forchione','ashlie.forchione@gmail.com','','50.4.160.142','2014-05-26 11:13:30','2014-05-26 15:13:30','So true, Andrea! Have you noticed how well ESPN integrates social media into their shows? \n\nSportsNation does a fantastic job in particular, but even feature pieces have a designated hashtag like #SCFeatured to unite conversation. Even the NFL draft this year created unique threads for the team that was picking – each appeared consistently (throughout commercials and the draft itself) in the bottom right corner of the screen; DETPick, for example. \n\nThanks for the article!',0,'1','','',0,0);
INSERT INTO `sandbox_comments` VALUES (21,3105,'Andrea Reynolds','andrea.reynolds2@gmail.com','','173.162.42.189','2014-05-27 14:33:34','2014-05-27 18:33:34','I have! SportsNation is one of my favorite programs that utilizes this combination. I was not aware of NFL draft social media adaptation, but I am not surprised! That makes perfect sense as it gives their audience (whom may not be near a TV) the chance to join in on the action and conversation in real time. Great example! Thanks for the comment :)',0,'1','','',20,1);
