INSERT INTO `sandbox_comments` VALUES (23,3139,'Andrea Reynolds','andrea.reynolds2@gmail.com','','173.162.42.189','2014-06-24 09:51:01','2014-06-24 13:51:01','Thank you, Divya! The post definitely served as an opportunity to do some much-needed research on Google Adwords and PPC, as they are integral parts in digital marketing. Thanks for stopping by our blog!',0,'1','','',22,1);
INSERT INTO `sandbox_comments` VALUES (24,3198,'Dave Linabury','dave@ingenexdigital.com','http://ingenexdigital.com','98.224.244.135','2014-07-10 08:21:33','2014-07-10 12:21:33','I would add the ability to write well, Derek. So many new marketers are graduating and assuming that a small amount of creativity and a knowledge of social media will get them an instant six figure income and a director\'s title. It won\'t. \n\nWriting well will always serve you well. My 2¢.',0,'1','','',0,0);
INSERT INTO `sandbox_comments` VALUES (25,3244,'Soumya Roy','soumyaroy.office@gmail.com','http://www.promozseo.com/','117.194.15.172','2014-08-19 11:32:31','2014-08-19 15:32:31','Nice article Andrea. Really good stuff and points are valid. I am an SEO by profession and a recent entrepreneur who just started his startup.\nI knew the basics of Pinterest and always suggested my clients to follow and maintain them to get the maximum out of this social sharing site. But when it came to my business, I am doing the same wrong things which you told not to do.\nI think the #1 &amp; #2 points are the most important. As a small team a startup always has few limitation on budget, resources etc. and that is the big problem for us right now. We started our Pinterest account with much enthusiasm and worked on it to develop but due to lack of resources and budget we are now falling behind the line.\nI, personally will really like to know your suggestions on social media especially for a startup company like us.\n\nRegards\nSoumya Roy',0,'1','','',0,0);
INSERT INTO `sandbox_comments` VALUES (26,3244,'Andrea Reynolds','andrea.reynolds2@gmail.com','','67.177.159.251','2014-08-19 14:39:28','2014-08-19 18:39:28','Thank you, Soumya Roy! I really appreciate your comment. I completely understand the limitations that go along with being a small business—we (Ingenex) are a small business, too!\n\nI would suggest prioritizing your social media accounts. While it\'s important to have a social presence, it\'s even more important to connect with your target audience. So, in terms of your Pinterest strategy, if you find that your target audience is more prevalent and active on, for example, Twitter and Linkedin, it\'s completely O.K. to cut out other social media platforms in order to focus your time, energy and resources on social media platforms where you will see results. Hope that helps!\n\nP.S. Here is a link to another article on social media strategy. It gives you pointers/tips on how to clarify your strategy: http://ingenexdigital.com/using-social-media-correctly/',0,'1','','',25,1);
